Our Mission is to democratise the global research industry by providing unbiased business intelligence through analysis of mass public data. Assisted by Machine Learning and NLP techniques, any company can now benefit from deep insights into markets, well beyond what human analysts can gather and digest in commercially viable time frames.




Since our Series A and B funding rounds in 2022, we have come a long way to now supplying data to multiple industry leading procurement and buyers platforms. Our clients now include multi-billion dollar global conglomerates; their experiences and deep industry insights revealed further efficiency gains within procurement waiting to be unlocked, through a combination of LLM solutions, bespoke classification models, and traditional data science methods, which we are trialing as a new product.




As such, our ‘Blue-Chip’ leadership team are looking for people who want to grow and develop with the company.




About the role

The role will be part of a team to maintain and develop NLP components in our Backend ETL pipeline, enabling our APIs and our native SaaS platform to have real time intelligence into a company's service and product offerings, and how it compares to its competitors within the trends of its market.




Distinct from our competitors, our services do not operate within a static data lake - instead, all of our analysis is performed on the fly, using a free text input provided by the user. You will not be transforming the same batch of data over and over again - you will be working with a dynamic stream of data, and no two days will be the same.




Join the engineering team at a small tech start-up, delivering market-leading supplier discovery intelligence with AI methods;
Working with our Junior Data Scientist to train and deploy in-house NLP models, including but not limited to BERT based text classification, key phrase extraction, and sentiment analysis;
Collaborate with the backend team to deploy and maintain new agentic deep-research and RAG applications for market and company analysis;
Design, build, test, ship, and monitor NLP analysis pipelines;
Create containerised workflows using pre-trained NLP/other ML models; API requests; and mathematical & statistical methods, with particular focus on text embeddings;
Work closely with backend team to architect and manage vector/graph/other databases;
Provide solutions in iterative steps, instead of waiting for a perfect solution;
Take ownership of a knowledge modelling project for information extraction by LLM.




We value cultural fit as much as technical skills. We are a small close-knit team - while everyone carries their own weight, we all share the same "can-do" attitude to help each other out as colleagues and friends. We also celebrate diversity in both culture, background and experience, bringing a wide range of perspectives from other industries into our work.




About you

You are a passionate and experienced NLP Data Scientist with a strong background in machine learning and natural language processing. You have a proven track record of developing and deploying NLP models in production environments, and you are excited about the opportunity to work with a dynamic and innovative team.




Key qualifications include:

Strong programming skills in Python and experience with NLP libraries such as Huggingface Transformers, SpaCy, Scikit-learn or NLTK;
Experienced with machine learning frameworks such as TensorFlow or PyTorch;
Experienced in the iterative cycle of data preparation, training and evaluating NLP models;
Sees it as a challenge to work within resource constraints in order to maintain financial viability of the company;
Strong communication skills and the ability to explain complex technical concepts to non-technical stakeholders;
A continued interest in the latest developments in NLP and machine learning, with a self-drive to experiment with new techniques and approaches.




Above all, we treasure people with insatiable curiosity. We treasure people who strive to be a better version of themselves every day, being motivated to find solutions whatever it takes. We believe that investing in an ever-growing individual will yield a better return than hiring a perfect fit.




What we offer

Competitive salary and equity options;
Flexible working hours and remote work options;
Room for personal and professional growth, with a focus on how you want to advance your career;
A friendly and inclusive work environment that is full of fun and camaraderie;
A 9 day fortnight work schedule, allowing you to have a Friday day off every two full-week cycle.
Yes, we do take these time off most if not all the time
No, this is not one of those "take as much time off as you want" policies that no one can actually use
